text: Gymnothorax equatorialis is a moray eel found in the eastern Pacific ocean, from the Gulf of California to Peru.Gymnothorax equatorialis at www.fishbase.org. It was first named by Hildebrand in 1946, and is commonly known as the spotted-tail moray or the spottail moray.Common names for Gymnothorax equatorialis at www.fishbase.org. ==References== equatorialis Category:Fish described in 1946
